<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: SMB USA (SMB2 USA) Restoration Hack]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11590&amp;p=133303#p133303"><![CDATA[
Okay. Here is a new build I created today which fixes two things. <br /><br />1. <div class="quotetitle">TRCF wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />The string &quot;ZELDA&quot; is present at ROM address 0x1FFFB. It appears that Nintendo copied the PRG footer/vector table from The Legend of Zelda (another FDS-to-NES conversion) and simply forgot to change the title.<br /></div><br /><br />^This has been corrected.<br /><br />2. I forgot to change to wording on the Game Over screen to say &quot;End&quot; instead of &quot;Retry&quot;. This now been corrected. It took me a year to realize I forgot this. &quot;Retry&quot; is really 'Engrish' in this case as you really don't retry anything but instead resets the game.<br /><br />Original, unhacked version: CRC16 = DE2A<br />In its hacked .nes file format: CRC16 = A221<br /><br />SEE BELOW FOR FINAL DOWNLOAD<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5262">ShaneM</a> — Sat Aug 30, 2014 2:22 pm</p><hr />
